## Avatar Selector Interface with Infinite Scrolling and Swipe Gesture

To create an Avatar Selector interface with seamless user experience and advanced highlighting feature using the createjs javascript library, we can follow the steps below:

1. Load the createjs library in our HTML file:

   ```html
   <script src="https://code.createjs.com/1.0.0/createjs.min.js"></script>
   ```

2. Create a canvas element and initialize the stage:

   ```html
   <canvas id="canvas"></canvas>
   ```

   ```javascript
   const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');
   const stage = new createjs.Stage(canvas);
   ```

3. Load the animal images and store them in an array:

   ```javascript
   const animals = [
     'lion.png',
     'elephant.png',
     'tiger.png',
     'panda.png',
     'giraffe.png',
     'monkey.png',
     'zebra.png',
     'crocodile.png',
     'hippo.png',
     'rhino.png'
   ];

   const loader = new createjs.LoadQueue(false);
   loader.loadManifest(animals.map(animal => ({ src: animal })));
   ```

4. Create a container for the avatars and add them to the stage:

   ```javascript
   const avatarContainer = new createjs.Container();
   avatarContainer.x = stage.canvas.width / 2;
   avatarContainer.y = stage.canvas.height / 2;
   stage.addChild(avatarContainer);

   loader.on('complete', () => {
     animals.forEach((animal, i) => {
       const bitmap = new createjs.Bitmap(loader.getResult(animal));
       bitmap.regX = bitmap.image.width / 2;
       bitmap.x = (i - (animals.length - 1) / 2) * (bitmap.image.width + 20);
       avatarContainer.addChild(bitmap);
     });
   });
   ```

5. Add event listeners for swipe gestures:

   ```javascript
   let startX, startY, isMoving = false;

   stage.addEventListener('stagemousedown', e => {
     startX = e.stageX;
     startY = e.stageY;
     isMoving = true;
   });

   stage.addEventListener('stagemouseup', e => {
     if (isMoving) {
       const diffX = e.stageX - startX;
       if (Math.abs(diffX) > 50) {
         avatarContainer.x += diffX > 0 ? -200 : 200;
       } else {
         avatarContainer.x = stage.canvas.width / 2;
       }
       isMoving = false;
     }
   });
   ```

6. Add a highlight box and checkmark button:

   ```javascript
   const highlightBox = new createjs.Shape();
   highlightBox.graphics.beginStroke('#000').setStrokeStyle(2).drawRect(-50, -50, 100, 100);
   avatarContainer.addChild(highlightBox);

   const checkmark = new createjs.Shape();
   checkmark.graphics.beginStroke('#000').setStrokeStyle(2).moveTo(-40, -20).lineTo(-20, 0).lineTo(30, -50);
   checkmark.x = stage.canvas.width / 2;
   checkmark.y = stage.canvas.height / 2 + 150;
   stage.addChild(checkmark);

   checkmark.addEventListener('click', () => {
     const selected = avatarContainer.getChildAt(Math.floor((avatarContainer.x - stage.canvas.width / 2) / -220));
     alert(`You selected ${animals[avatarContainer.getChildIndex(selected)]}!`);
   });
   ```

7. Add a ticker to enable infinite scrolling:

   ```javascript
   createjs.Ticker.framerate = 60;
   createjs.Ticker.on('tick', () => {
     if (avatarContainer.x > stage.canvas.width / 2 + 100) {
       avatarContainer.x = -stage.canvas.width / 2 - 100;
     } else if (avatarContainer.x < -stage.canvas.width / 2 - 100) {
       avatarContainer.x = stage.canvas.width / 2 + 100;
     }
     const selected = avatarContainer.getChildAt(Math.floor((avatarContainer.x - stage.canvas.width / 2) / -220));
     highlightBox.x = selected.x;
     highlightBox.y = selected.y;
   });
   ```

The above code sample creates an Avatar Selector interface with ten unique animal images that can be easily selected by users to be used as avatars on the Gameboard. The interface allows for infinite scrolling, enabling the avatars to scroll seamlessly from left to right and vice versa. Users can smoothly scroll between avatars using a swipe gesture in either the right or left direction. Additionally, an auxiliary checkmark button is placed below the highlighted box, which users can press to confirm their avatar selection.

